p: The FA compositions of the breast muscle tissues are shown in Table 12 and Table 13. The fat content of the breast was not affected ( p > 0.05). However, significant differences were registered for most SFAs. TM oil supplementation decreased the content of C12:0 ( p < 0.001), C16:0 ( p < 0.001), C18:0 ( p < 0.001) and C23:0 ( p = 0.002) and increased C14:0 ( p < 0.001), C15:0 ( p < 0.001), C17:0 ( p < 0.001), C20:0 ( p = 0.001), C21:0 ( p < 0.001) and C24:0 ( p = 0.019). Moreover, TM oil supplementation reduced the level of most MUFAs, such as C14:1 ( p < 0.001), C16:1 ( p < 0.001), C18:1 c9 ( p < 0.001), C18:1 c11 ( p < 0.001), C22:1 n-9 ( p < 0.001) and C24:1 ( p = 0.003). The PUFA content was also affected by the dietary treatments, and TM oil supplementation showed the highest values for C18:2 c9c12 ( p < 0.001), C18:3 c9c12c15 ( p < 0.001) and C20:5 n-3 ( p < 0.001) and the lowest values for C18:3 n-6 ( p = 0.002), C20:2 ( p < 0.001) and C22:2 ( p < 0.001).
